### getSubRangeForMask() {#a8e3cbbade7440fd10534f580ee6f2d06}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>const LiveInterval::SubRange &amp; getSubRangeForMask (<a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/lanebitmask">LaneBitmask</a> LM, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/liveinterval">LiveInterval</a> &amp; LI)</>}>
Find a subrange corresponding to the lane mask <code>LM</code>, or a superset of it, in the live interval <code>LI</code>.

The interval <code>LI</code> is assumed to contain such a subrange. This function is used to find corresponding subranges between the original interval and the new intervals.
